---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';

const bullets = [
  'Designed and maintained the visual identity system used across all Edge Network channels.',
  'Produced weekly Discord recap graphics to keep the community engaged and aligned on direction and progress.',
  'Created campaign assets for major announcements, partnerships, and product launches.',
  'Developed content strategy and wrote copy across X/Twitter, LinkedIn, and Discord.',
  'Designed branded merchandise including hoodies, shirts, and accessories.',
  'Built content templates to help the core team produce consistent on-brand material independently.',
];
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="Edge Network"
  description="Brand, content and design for a decentralized cloud infrastructure project. Visual identity, campaigns, merch and a weekly Discord recap."
  tags={['content', 'design', 'comms']}
  meta={[
    { label: 'Role',   value: 'Brand & Content Designer' },
    { label: 'Client', value: 'Edge Network'              },
    { label: 'Year',   value: '2026'                      },
  ]}
  heroImage="/img-edge-01.jpg"
  images={[
    '/img-edge-02.jpg',
    '/img-edge-03.jpg',
    '/img-edge-04.jpg',
    '/img-edge-05.jpg',
    '/img-edge-06.jpg',
    '/img-edge-07.jpg',
    '/img-edge-08.jpg',
    '/img-edge-09.jpg',
  ]}
  linkLabel="view twitter profile"
  linkHref="https://x.com/edgenetwork"
>

  <section class="case-section">
    <h2 class="case-section__title">The context</h2>
    <p>Edge Network is a decentralized cloud infrastructure project built to challenge centralised providers — offering edge computing, storage, and CDN services powered by a distributed node network. I worked with their core team over an extended engagement to build and sustain their brand voice, content strategy, and visual identity across social channels, community platforms, and physical merchandise.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="case-section">
    <h2 class="case-section__title">The problem</h2>
    <p>Technical infrastructure is hard to market. Edge Network had a genuinely strong product — decentralised, fast, cost-efficient — but their content wasn't translating that for a broader audience. Social posts felt generic, campaigns lacked a cohesive identity, and the community wasn't growing as fast as the product deserved. The team needed someone who could hold the visual and editorial thread across everything they shipped publicly.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="case-section">
    <h2 class="case-section__title">What I did</h2>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      {bullets.map(item => (
        <li class="bullet-list__item">
          <img src="/icon-bullet-list.svg" alt="" aria-hidden="true" class="bullet-list__icon" width="8" height="8" />
          <span>{item}</span>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="case-section">
    <h2 class="case-section__title">The result</h2>
    <p>A more cohesive brand presence across all channels. The visual language became recognisable enough that community members could identify Edge Network content at a glance. The Discord recaps became a weekly community ritual, and campaign assets supported partnership announcements that reached tens of thousands of people. The content system I left behind let the team keep the momentum going independently.</p>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>
